description:
This tutorial teaches you how to fix your 4-way mobavators so that they work with the recent Beta 1.6 patch. It also teaches you how to build the new working version from scratch.

I explain how you can modify the mobavator to make it transport cows, sheep, pigs, and wolves effectively. We look at how to attach multiple layers to a single mobavator. Finally we quickly consider how to build simple 4-way mobavators for a 1x1 shaft, which is useful if your are transporting mobs using 1 wide tubes or canals.

This 4-way mobavator is based on the original mobavator I saw in this video: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HezgBRwlRvI

To learn how I built the hostile mob system shown in this video, watch this hostile mob system tutorial: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=f8YJfAwYOz0

For a simple hostile mob killing mechanism and loot collection system, watch this video: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=n2Mv-nIky2A

A special thanks is deserving to both Bohnmeal and Kasfexr for pointing out the simple fix for getting the mobavator working again after Beta 1.6+.
